Battle Bot ESP32 API Guide
Base Address

All API routes are hosted on the ESP32 web server.

Example:

http://10.10.10.10/

Control API
/processcontrol

Controls motors and servos.

Method
GET
Parameters
Parameter	Range	Description
M1	-255 to 255	Motor 1 speed and direction
M2	-255 to 255	Motor 2 speed and direction
S1	0 to 180	Servo 1 position
S2	0 to 180	Servo 2 position
Motor Direction
Value	Action
Positive	Forward
Negative	Reverse
0	Stop

Values between -5 and 5 are treated as zero.

Examples
Drive forward
/processcontrol?M1=255&M2=255
Turn left
/processcontrol?M1=-255&M2=255
Stop motors
/processcontrol?M1=0&M2=0
Move servo
/processcontrol?S1=90
Combined request
/processcontrol?M1=120&M2=120&S1=45
Response
done
Telemetry API
/quickstatus

Returns live battery voltage and internal temperature.

Method
GET
Response
{
  "result":"pass",
  "vIn":4.82,
  "temperature":31.25
}
Battery Charging Detection

If:

vIn > 4.5V

then the unit is considered charging.

Settings API
/getsettings

Returns a stored setting value.

Method
GET
Parameters
Parameter	Description
key	Setting key
Example
/getsettings?key=AP
Response
{
  "result":"pass",
  "key":"AP",
  "value":"BattleBot"
}
Update Settings API
/updatesettings

Updates a stored setting.

Method
GET
Parameters
Parameter	Description
key	Setting key
value	New value
Example
/updatesettings?key=AP&value=BattleBot
Response
Updated successfully
File System API
/files

Returns all files stored on the ESP32 filesystem.

Method
GET
Response Example
{
  "used":123456,
  "total":1048576,
  "files":[
    {
      "id":0,
      "name":"index.html",
      "size":1024
    },
    {
      "id":1,
      "name":"control.html",
      "size":4096
    }
  ]
}
Upload API
/upload

Uploads files to the ESP32 filesystem.

Method
POST
Multipart Form Field
file
Example HTML
<form action="/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <input type="file" name="file">
  <input type="submit">
</form>
Delete File API
/delete

Deletes a file from the filesystem.

Method
GET
Parameters
Parameter	Description
file	Filename
Example
/delete?file=index.html
Response
Deleted
System Information API
/systeminfo

Returns system information as HTML.

Includes
free RAM
filesystem usage
MAC address
uptime
flash size
firmware version
battery voltage
temperature
Version API
/getver

Returns firmware version string.

Example Response
ver:kijaniv1
Factory Reset API
/reset

Factory resets the unit.

Method
GET
Parameters
Parameter	Description
factory_reset	Required
Example
/reset?factory_reset=1
Static File Hosting

The ESP32 serves all files stored in LittleFS.

Example:

/index.html
/control.html
/loading.gif
/style.css
